issue in which <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Microsoft</ENAMEX> has a huge financial stake, I think the least we
<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">readers</ENAMEX> can ask is that you take care to learn the basic facts of the matter
and check that what's in the article is at least remotely plausible.

            -- <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Daniel</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Weinreb</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Arlington</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Mass.</ENAMEX>

            
               <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Andrew</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Shuman</ENAMEX> replies: This letter is one of the nicer ones I have received in the
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">past two weeks</TIMEX>. I had <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">two</NUMEX> goals for my article: <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">first</NUMEX>, to explain what <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Java</ENAMEX> is;
